Generate the autocompletion script for the bash shell.

This script depends on the 'bash-completion' package.
If it is not installed already, you can install it via your OS's package manager.

To load completions in your current shell session:

	source <(agentclash completion bash)

To load completions for every new session, execute once:

#### Linux:

	agentclash completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/agentclash

#### macOS:

	agentclash completion bash > $(brew --prefix)/etc/bash_completion.d/agentclash

You will need to start a new shell for this setup to take effect.

Usage:
  agentclash completion bash

Flags:
  -h, --help              help for bash
      --no-descriptions   disable completion descriptions

Global Flags:
      --api-url string     API base URL (overrides config)
      --json               Output in JSON format
      --no-color           Disable color output
      --non-interactive    Disable interactive prompts (also honored: CI=true, AGENTCLASH_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, --json, no TTY)
  -o, --output string      Output format: table, json, yaml
  -q, --quiet              Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose            Enable debug output on stderr
  -w, --workspace string   Workspace ID (overrides config)
      --yes                Skip confirmation prompts
